Real Madrid coach Carlo Ancelotti is committed to the Brazil job, it has been reported. ESPN says Ancelotti has agreed with the CBF to take over as Brazil coach from July 2023. The Real Madrid manager would have committed to the Canarinha until 2026, when the next World Cup ends. The Brazilian players inside the Real squad are aware of the situation of their coach. The details of the contract are being discussed, but the parties have no intention of announcing the agreement because the Italian has a contract with Real Madrid until 2024.